# === Source: commit.txt ===
pchunk:commit.txt:2d167687 | cluster:cluster_1 | 0.63 | unsupervised | py,runtime,base,class | fix(types): fix runtime attr bugs, align base sigs, clean mypy (v0.4.1) Fixes three runtime bugs uncovered by enabling follow_untyped_imports: - adapter.py: stats() accessed .node_count/.edge_count as attrs on the   dict returned by kg.stats(); correct keys are "total_nodes"/"total_edges" - snapshots.py: save_snapshot() dropped `force` kwarg from base class   (TypeError for callers using force=True); return type Path → Path | None - snapshots.py: capture() positional order was inverted vs base class;   added hotspots/issues params forwarded to super() Also: - Migrate pyproject.toml to PEP 621 [project] table; kg-snapshot added   as required runtime dep (git source, replaces optional kg_rag) - CLI --db/--lancedb default to None, resolved relative to --repo at   runtime — single-flag invocations now work correctly - follow_untyped_imports = true in mypy overrides for kg_snapshot.* - Remove stale # type: ignore[misc] on class defs; add cast() at   attribute-access sites in cmd_snapshot.py and test_query.py - Add .pycodekg/ to .gitignore (pycodekg index, parallel to .codekg/) - Bump version to 0.4.1
pchunk:commit.txt:7282d700 | cluster:cluster_7 | 0.57 | unsupervised | anthropic,claude,co-authored-by,com | Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

