# === Source: docs/ftreekg_packaging_fix.md ===
# Section: Problem Summary
pchunk:docs/ftreekg_packaging_fix.md:e7f4024a | cluster:cluster_5 | 0.70 | unsupervised | any,cannot,dependency,due | FTreeKG cannot be reliably installed as a path dependency from kgrag (or any other repo) due to two structural issues in its `pyproject.toml`. ---
pchunk:docs/ftreekg_packaging_fix.md:c4e89f06 | cluster:cluster_1 | 0.63 | unsupervised | src,cli,toml,cmd_query | **File:** `pyproject.toml` line 13 **Current:** ```toml packages = [{include = "src"}] ``` **Problem:** This tells Poetry to install a top-level package named `src`. The code lives directly inside `src/` with no `ftree_kg/` subdirectory, so the installed import path is `import src` — which collides with any other package using the same flat layout, and is not importable by a meaningful name.  **All CLI entry points are also broken as a result:** ```toml ftreekg        = "src.cli:cli" ftreekg-build  = "src.cli.cmd_build:build" ftreekg-query  = "src.cli.cmd_query:query" ftreekg-pack   = "src.cli.cmd_query:pack" ftreekg-analyze = "src.cli.cmd_analyze:analyze" ftreekg-snapshot = "src.cli.cmd_snapshot:snapshot" ```  ---
pchunk:docs/ftreekg_packaging_fix.md:4c9a97d8 | cluster:cluster_5 | 0.68 | unsupervised | kgrag,depends,ftree-kg,git | **File:** `pyproject.toml` line 35 **Current:** ```toml kg-rag = { git = "https://github.com/Flux-Frontiers/KGRAG.git"} ``` **Problem:** kgrag depends on ftree-kg, and ftree-kg depends on kg-rag → circular. Poetry/pip resolvers will either fail or silently install mismatched versions. FTreeKG should depend on `code-kg` and `doc-kg` directly (as it already does on lines 36–37), not on the kgrag orchestrator.  ---
pchunk:docs/ftreekg_packaging_fix.md:11740573 | cluster:cluster_1 | 0.61 | unsupervised | py,adapter,cli,config | src/   __init__.py   adapter.py   cli/   config.py   extractor.py   module.py   snapshots.py   tests/
pchunk:docs/ftreekg_packaging_fix.md:3c6185dd | cluster:cluster_1 | 0.64 | unsupervised | py,src,tests,adapter | src/   ftree_kg/     __init__.py     adapter.py     cli/     config.py     extractor.py     module.py     snapshots.py   tests/   ← move tests out of src ```
pchunk:docs/ftreekg_packaging_fix.md:e4c675c4 | cluster:cluster_3 | 0.66 | unsupervised | cli,ftree_kg,cmd_query,analyze | [tool.poetry.scripts] ftreekg          = "ftree_kg.cli:cli" ftreekg-build    = "ftree_kg.cli.cmd_build:build" ftreekg-query    = "ftree_kg.cli.cmd_query:query" ftreekg-pack     = "ftree_kg.cli.cmd_query:pack" ftreekg-analyze  = "ftree_kg.cli.cmd_analyze:analyze" ftreekg-snapshot = "ftree_kg.cli.cmd_snapshot:snapshot"
pchunk:docs/ftreekg_packaging_fix.md:dbc848c2 | cluster:cluster_3 | 0.65 | unsupervised | git,com,flux-frontiers,github | [tool.poetry.dependencies] python   = ">=3.12,<3.14" click    = "^8.1.0" code-kg  = { git = "https://github.com/Flux-Frontiers/code_kg.git" } doc-kg   = { git = "https://github.com/Flux-Frontiers/doc_kg.git" } ```
pchunk:docs/ftreekg_packaging_fix.md:2feaa982 | cluster:cluster_1 | 0.62 | unsupervised | import,xxx,ftree_kg,src | All files that currently do `from src.xxx import ...` or `import src.xxx` must be updated to `from ftree_kg.xxx import ...` / `import ftree_kg.xxx`.
pchunk:docs/ftreekg_packaging_fix.md:011dc9d9 | cluster:cluster_1 | 0.63 | unsupervised | code_kg,ftree_kg,ignore_missing_imports,kg_rag | ```toml [[tool.mypy.overrides]] module = ["code_kg.*", "kg_rag.*", "ftree_kg.*"] ignore_missing_imports = true ```
pchunk:docs/ftreekg_packaging_fix.md:352700b4 | cluster:cluster_3 | 0.66 | unsupervised | cd,egs,ftree_kg,ftreekg | ```bash cd /Users/egs/repos/FTreeKG poetry install ftreekg --help   # verify CLI resolves cd /Users/egs/repos/kgrag poetry update ftree-kg python -c "import ftree_kg; print(ftree_kg.__version__)" ``` ---
pchunk:docs/ftreekg_packaging_fix.md:268f77a4 | cluster:cluster_1 | 0.63 | unsupervised | src,include,code_kg,doc_kg | All other packages in this ecosystem follow the same layout: | Repo     | packages declaration                          | Import root | |----------|-----------------------------------------------|-------------| | code_kg  | `{include = "code_kg", from = "src"}`         | `code_kg`   | | doc_kg   | `{include = "doc_kg", from = "src"}`          | `doc_kg`    | | kgrag    | `{include = "kg_rag", from = "src"}`          | `kg_rag`    | | FTreeKG  | `{include = "src"}` ← **broken, fix this**   | `src` ← bad | ---
pchunk:docs/ftreekg_packaging_fix.md:9b3dea66 | cluster:cluster_5 | 0.70 | unsupervised | ftreekg,path,because,correct | - kgrag `pyproject.toml` currently has: `ftree-kg = {path = "../FTreeKG", develop = true}` - This path dep is correct; the problem is entirely inside FTreeKG itself - Fix was deferred because source files were staged at time of discovery (2026-03-25)

